verbose_text: Transient destabilization of acto-myosin cytoskeleton by inhibition of myosin II or depolymerization of actin promoted polarization of EC against the flow, indicating that an intact acto-myosin cytoskeleton resists flow induced polarization.
evidence: acto-myosin cytoskeleton by inhibition of myosin II or depolymerization of actin promoted polarization of EC
